data.title: WEDDINGS; Mariana Stockly, Benjamin Tupper
data.text:
Mariana du Pont Stockly, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. A. Holmes Stockly of Falmouth, Me., was married there yesterday to Benjamin Thomas Tupper, a son of Mr. and Mrs. Ansel N. Tupper of South Portland, Me. The Rev. Frederick Lipp, a Unitarian Universalist minister, performed the ceremony at the home of the bride's parents.

Mrs. Tupper is an English teacher at Orono (Me.) Junior High School. She graduated from Brown University and received a master's degree in education from the University of New Hampshire. Mr. Tupper graduated from the University of Maine, where he is a candidate for a master's degree in quaternary studies.
